U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION]

00:42.459 --> 00:45.003
THAT WAS A HOOT!

00:59.976 --> 01:02.520
(<i> shears clipping</i> )

01:03.646 --> 01:05.022
(<i> Ed Bighead humming</i> )

01:05.105 --> 01:06.024
♪ AH DOO-DOO-DOO ♪

01:06.107 --> 01:06.983
♪ DOO DOO DOO ♪

01:07.066 --> 01:08.943
♪ FROGGY LADY, OH! ♪

01:09.027 --> 01:11.029
♪ DOO DOO DOO,
DA-DA-DA DOO ♪

01:11.112 --> 01:13.031
♪ FROGGY LADY... ♪

01:13.114 --> 01:14.073
(<i> squish</i> )

01:14.157 --> 01:15.200
(<i> gasps</i> )

01:16.075 --> 01:19.412
(<i> popping</i> )

01:19.496 --> 01:20.663
ROCKO!

01:20.747 --> 01:21.873
YES, MR. BIGHEAD?

01:21.956 --> 01:25.210
MAY I HAVE A WORD
WITH YOU, PLEASE?

01:25.293 --> 01:26.920
YES, MR. BIGHEAD?

01:27.003 --> 01:29.881
YOUR DOG HAS MADE
A MESS OF MY YARD!

01:29.964 --> 01:31.841
(<i> popping</i> )

01:31.925 --> 01:32.884
OH, MR. BIGHEAD

01:32.967 --> 01:35.887
THAT'S JUST SPUNKY'S WAY
OF SAYING HE LOVES YOU.

01:35.970 --> 01:37.889
WELL, I HAVE ENOUGH
LOVE IN MY YARD

01:37.972 --> 01:39.891
TO MAKE MY DEAD
GRANDMOTHER GIGGLE

01:39.974 --> 01:42.185
YOU SNIVELING
NEIGHBORHOOD MENACE!

01:43.436 --> 01:46.189
{\an1}AND I DON'T WANT TO STEP IN
ANY MORE OF YOUR LOVE...

01:46.272 --> 01:47.398
ED!

01:47.482 --> 01:49.025
BAD!

01:49.108 --> 01:49.943
DOWN!

01:50.026 --> 01:51.027
(<i> squeaks</i> )

01:51.110 --> 01:52.028
BACK!

01:52.111 --> 01:52.278
(<i> squeaks again</i> )

01:54.072 --> 01:55.365
ROCKO, DARLING

01:55.448 --> 01:56.825
YOU REALLY
MUST LEARN

01:56.908 --> 01:59.577
TO STAND UP TO
MR. BIGHEAD, DEAR.

01:59.661 --> 02:02.872
{\an1}WELL, I'M NOT VERY GOOD
AT CONFRONTATIONS.

02:02.956 --> 02:04.916
OF COURSE YOU AREN'T,
DARLING.

02:04.999 --> 02:08.044
AND TRY TO KEEP SCRUFFY
OFF THE LAWN

02:08.127 --> 02:09.127
WOULD YOU, DEAR?

02:09.211 --> 02:10.045
Whose show is it?

02:10.128 --> 02:11.005
{\an1}(<i> rings</i> )

02:11.089 --> 02:12.549
Both:
I'LL GET IT.

02:12.632 --> 02:13.716
{\an1}(<i> in Australian accent</i> ):
ROCKO'S MODERN HOME.

02:13.800 --> 02:16.177
ROCKO SPEAKING.

02:16.261 --> 02:17.762
OH, HI, MUM.

02:17.846 --> 02:18.263
I MEAN, GOOD DAY.

02:20.014 --> 02:22.058
LET ME SAY SOMETHING.

02:22.141 --> 02:25.395
HEY, HEY, I'VE GOT
A SHRIMP ON THE BARBY.

02:25.478 --> 02:27.063
(<i> giggles</i> )

02:27.146 --> 02:28.815
WHAT'S THAT, MUM?

02:28.898 --> 02:30.316
HE'S COMING WHEN?

02:30.400 --> 02:33.987
OH, YES, THAT WOULD
BE LOVELY... MATE.

02:34.070 --> 02:35.155
♪<i> ALOUETTE</i> ♪

02:35.238 --> 02:37.323
♪<i> GENTILE ALOUETTE.</i> ♪

02:37.407 --> 02:39.158
YOU TOO, MUM. BYE.

02:39.242 --> 02:40.034
CIAO.

02:40.118 --> 02:41.286
(<i> door opens</i> )

02:42.328 --> 02:43.329
WHO WAS THAT?

02:43.413 --> 02:45.123
OH, YOUR MOM.

02:45.206 --> 02:46.124
MY MOM?

02:46.207 --> 02:47.250
WHAT DID SHE WANT?

02:47.333 --> 02:50.128
UM, SHE SAID
SHE LOVES YOU

02:50.211 --> 02:51.754
SHE MISSES YOU...

02:52.672 --> 02:54.424
{\an1}OH, AND SOME GUY
NAMED DINGO

02:54.507 --> 02:56.759
{\an1}IS COMING TO VISIT YOU
ON SATURDAY.

02:56.843 --> 02:57.760
DINGO?!

02:57.844 --> 02:59.554
DINGO'S COMING!

02:59.637 --> 03:00.680
LOCK THE DOOR!

03:01.347 --> 03:02.432
CLOSE THE CURTAINS!

03:02.515 --> 03:05.435
I SAID, LOCK THE DOORS!

03:05.518 --> 03:09.439
AND FOR THE LOVE OF CAKE,
HIDE ME!

03:11.190 --> 03:13.109
ROCKO, YOU'RE SCARING US!

03:13.192 --> 03:14.903
WHO'S DINGO?

03:14.986 --> 03:17.030
(<i> inhales deeply</i> )

03:17.113 --> 03:19.991
DINGO WAS THE MEANEST
THIRD GRADER IN THE WHOLE WORLD.

03:20.074 --> 03:21.951
ARE YOU GOING TO HAVE
A FLASHBACK?

03:22.035 --> 03:23.328
(<i> catching breath</i> )

03:23.411 --> 03:24.954
YES.

03:25.038 --> 03:25.955
(<i> bell rings</i> )

03:26.039 --> 03:27.624
<i>ON THE VERY FIRST DAY</i>

03:27.707 --> 03:30.376
<i>DINGO MADE MY LIFE</i>
<i>AT FAIR DINKUM PRIMARY SCHOOL</i>

03:30.460 --> 03:31.711
<i>A LIVING NIGHTMARE.</i>

03:32.795 --> 03:33.379
HELLO.

03:35.798 --> 03:37.550
(<i> students tittering</i> )

03:37.634 --> 03:40.511
<i>AND FOR 12 TERRIBLE YEARS</i>
<i>I WAS KICKED...</i>

03:40.595 --> 03:41.638
<i>POKED...</i>

03:41.721 --> 03:42.972
<i>TRIPPED....</i>

03:43.056 --> 03:43.848
<i>THONKED...</i>

03:43.932 --> 03:45.141
<i>THWACKED....</i>

03:45.224 --> 03:46.809
<i>AND THWANKLED...</i>

03:46.893 --> 03:50.021
<i>RIGHT UP TO THE DAY</i>
<i>WHEN I FINALLY LEFT FOR AMERICA.</i>

03:50.104 --> 03:52.482
(<i> gentle jangling</i> )

03:52.565 --> 03:54.192
(<i> sighs</i> )

03:54.275 --> 03:55.485
{\an3}YOO-HOO!

03:55.568 --> 03:56.778
{\an3}SHORT-O.

04:03.493 --> 04:06.913
{\an5}Dingo:
I'VE GOT A GOING-AWAY
PRESENT FOR YOU.

04:14.796 --> 04:17.005
I'LL GET YOU SOME DAY, SHRIMP-O!

04:17.089 --> 04:19.384
(<i> jingling, rattling</i> )

04:20.426 --> 04:23.012
{\an1}<i>WHY HE NEVER LIKED ME,</i>
<i>I'LL NEVER KNOW.</i>

04:23.096 --> 04:25.181
AND DINGO WAS HIS NAME.

04:25.264 --> 04:26.516
OH.

04:25.264 --> 04:26.516
OH.

04:27.517 --> 04:29.477
(<i> crickets chirping</i> )

04:31.980 --> 04:33.523
(<i> blowing whistles loudly</i> )

04:34.315 --> 04:35.441
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO!

04:35.525 --> 04:36.317
HUP, TWO,
THREE, FOUR.

04:37.944 --> 04:42.532
(<i> blowing whistle</i> )

04:42.615 --> 04:46.619
DO YOU WANT TO BE A WIMP
YOUR WHOLE LIFE?

04:47.120 --> 04:48.037
YES, SIR.

04:48.121 --> 04:52.125
{\an5}DO YOU WANT TO LEARN
TO FIGHT LIKE A MAN?

04:52.208 --> 04:53.376
NO, SIR.

04:53.459 --> 04:54.419
GOOD!

04:54.502 --> 04:57.171
(<i> blowing whistle</i> )

05:04.178 --> 05:06.389
(<i> toots</i> )

05:06.472 --> 05:08.433
DROP AND GIVE ME 30!

05:09.600 --> 05:10.768
(<i> tooting</i> )

05:10.852 --> 05:12.311
(<i> grunting</i> )

05:12.395 --> 05:13.312
(<i> grunting</i> )

05:13.396 --> 05:15.064
(<i> tooting</i> )

05:15.148 --> 05:16.065
ONE...

05:16.149 --> 05:18.985
HEY! WHY AM I TAKING ORDERS
FROM YOU?

05:19.068 --> 05:22.071
BECAUSE YOU'RE
IN TRAINING!

05:22.155 --> 05:23.906
HI, SLEEPYHEAD.

05:23.990 --> 05:25.074
HI, FILBURT.

05:25.158 --> 05:27.076
ROCKO, YOU'VE GOT 24 HOURS

05:27.160 --> 05:30.079
TO PREPARE
FOR THE FIGHT OF YOUR LIFE!

05:30.163 --> 05:31.080
FIGHT?!

05:31.164 --> 05:32.415
I'M NOT GOING TO FIGHT!

05:32.498 --> 05:34.000
I'M GOING TO LEAVE TOWN.

05:34.083 --> 05:35.918
I'VE GOT TO GET
TO THE AIRPORT!

05:36.002 --> 05:37.253
SPUNKY!
COME ON, BOY!

05:37.336 --> 05:38.629
{\an3}GET HIM!

05:38.713 --> 05:39.630
GOTCHA.

05:39.714 --> 05:41.174
NO, PLEASE!

05:41.257 --> 05:45.178
{\an1}ROCKO, THE TIME HAS COME
TO STAND UP FOR WHAT'S RIGHT.

05:46.804 --> 05:52.185
{\an5}(<i> bellowing</i> ):
IN THE ART OF WAR,
ONE MUST KNOW HIS ENEMY.

05:52.268 --> 05:55.188
EH, DINGO'S FROM AUSTRALIA.

05:55.271 --> 05:56.355
WHATEVER!

05:57.440 --> 05:58.441
THROUGH THE USE

05:58.524 --> 06:01.027
OF SOPHISTICATED
COMPUTER TECHNOLOGY

06:01.110 --> 06:02.236
AND A BOX OF CRAYONS

06:02.320 --> 06:05.156
WE HAVE CONSTRUCTED
A LIKENESS OF DINGO

06:05.239 --> 06:06.824
AS HE WOULD APPEAR TODAY.

06:06.908 --> 06:07.825
FILBURT!

06:07.909 --> 06:08.409
AYE-AYE, CAPTAIN.

06:09.702 --> 06:12.288
TA-DA!

06:12.371 --> 06:13.831
(<i> screams</i> )

06:13.915 --> 06:18.169
{\an1}IT IS BECAUSE OF THIS REALLY
SCARY AND REALISTIC IMAGE

06:18.252 --> 06:21.631
THAT WE MUST PREPARE
TO FACE THE ENEMY!

06:21.714 --> 06:22.840
(<i> cracking</i> )

06:22.924 --> 06:23.883
OW.

06:24.217 --> 06:26.010
LESSON ONE:

06:26.094 --> 06:27.887
THE FIRST ENCOUNTER.

06:27.970 --> 06:30.223
{\an1}(<i> in Australian accent</i> ):
HELLO, THERE, DINGO.

06:30.306 --> 06:31.974
GOOD TO SEE YOU, EH?

06:32.058 --> 06:35.269
{\an1}(<i> in Australian accent</i> ):
I'VE COME TO GET YOU, ROCKO.

06:35.353 --> 06:38.856
{\an1}I OFFER YOU THESE FLOWERS,
IN PEACE AND GOODWILL.

06:38.940 --> 06:40.650
IS THIS A TRICK?

06:40.733 --> 06:42.652
HA, HA, HA, HA.

06:42.735 --> 06:45.154
NO!

06:45.238 --> 06:47.490
OH, HEFFER, THEY'RE BEAUTIFUL.

06:49.367 --> 06:52.161
THEN WHEN THE ENEMY
IS PREOCCUPIED

06:52.245 --> 06:53.329
GRAB SOMETHING BIG

06:53.412 --> 06:54.997
AND LET HIM HAVE IT!

06:55.081 --> 06:56.499
(<i> loud thud</i> )

06:57.792 --> 07:01.712
HEY, ROMEO, YOU LEFT SOMETHING
IN THE TOP DRAWER.

07:01.796 --> 07:03.172
YEAH?

07:03.881 --> 07:05.216
HELLO.

07:05.299 --> 07:06.259
HI!

07:06.342 --> 07:08.344
(<i> shrieks in pain</i> )

07:08.427 --> 07:10.179
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

07:10.263 --> 07:12.014
I THINK I'M AFRAID.

07:12.098 --> 07:15.643
{\an4}(<i> muffled</i> ):
ROCKO, BY THE TIME
WE'RE THROUGH WITH YOU

07:15.726 --> 07:18.855
{\an1}YOU'RE GOING TO BE
A SAVAGE, BLOODTHIRSTY BEAST.

07:20.189 --> 07:25.278
(<i> no dialogue</i> )

07:30.366 --> 07:32.451
(<i> loud thuds</i> )

07:45.464 --> 07:47.383
(<i> munching loudly</i> )

07:49.802 --> 07:52.388
HAJIMAY!

07:52.471 --> 07:54.599
HI...

07:54.682 --> 07:56.434
YA...

07:56.517 --> 07:57.393
{\an1}CHOY!

07:57.476 --> 07:59.145
(<i> screams</i> )

07:59.228 --> 08:01.564
(<i> chewing savagely</i> )

08:01.647 --> 08:02.899
ROCKO!

08:02.982 --> 08:05.902
YOU'RE A SAVAGE,
BLOODTHIRSTY BEAST!

08:05.985 --> 08:07.570
HELLO, MATES.

08:07.653 --> 08:10.907
HERE I AM TO BEAT YOU UP.

08:10.990 --> 08:12.742
OH, MY GOSH!

08:12.825 --> 08:14.368
IT'S DINGO!

08:14.452 --> 08:17.413
OLLIE, OLLIE, OXEN FREE.

08:17.496 --> 08:19.248
SIC HIM ROCKO, SIC HIM!

08:19.332 --> 08:21.000
(<i> growling</i> )

08:21.083 --> 08:22.919
YEAH!

08:23.002 --> 08:25.504
(<i> roaring</i> )

08:25.588 --> 08:28.341
(<i> Rocko snarling savagely</i> )

08:28.424 --> 08:29.342
FILBURT!

08:29.425 --> 08:29.634
PLAY DEAD!

08:31.969 --> 08:33.929
(<i> screams</i> )

08:34.013 --> 08:36.265
(<i> growling</i> )

08:37.725 --> 08:39.018
(<i> screaming</i> )

08:39.101 --> 08:40.061
DOWN, BOY!

08:41.145 --> 08:43.147
(<i> snarling fiercely</i> )

08:43.231 --> 08:44.857
(<i> skidding</i> )

08:46.859 --> 08:48.945
FILBURT, TALK TO ME.

08:49.028 --> 08:50.947
(<i> moaning</i> )

08:52.156 --> 08:54.784
HANG IN THERE, BUDDY.

08:54.867 --> 08:56.410
YOU'LL BE OKAY.

08:56.494 --> 08:57.954
(<i> car doors closing</i> )

09:02.667 --> 09:05.753
(<i> crickets chirping</i> )

09:21.102 --> 09:23.688
(<i> munching loudly</i> )

09:23.771 --> 09:25.398
(<i> gulps</i> )

09:25.481 --> 09:27.066
SNARL!

09:27.567 --> 09:29.568
Both:
HE'S READY!

09:34.448 --> 09:35.658
(<i> Japanese music playing</i> )

09:37.243 --> 09:39.287
I <i> AM</i> READY.

09:39.370 --> 09:40.705
(<i> loud snapping</i> )

09:46.002 --> 09:48.337
REMEMBER ALL
THAT I'VE TAUGHT YOU

09:48.421 --> 09:49.588
AND YOU WILL TRIUMPH.

09:49.672 --> 09:52.174
{\an1}AND IF THINGS
START TO GET IFFY

09:52.258 --> 09:53.759
KICK HIM IN THE HINEY.

09:53.843 --> 09:54.760
(<i> doorbell rings</i> )

09:54.844 --> 09:55.928
(<i> loud knocking</i> )

09:56.012 --> 09:57.305
(<i> Filburt and Heffer gasp</i> )

09:58.472 --> 10:00.266
I AM READY.

10:00.349 --> 10:03.352
(<i> knocking continues</i> )

10:14.113 --> 10:16.741
FRIEND ROCKO.

10:16.824 --> 10:18.534
OH...

10:18.617 --> 10:19.702
DINGO?

10:19.785 --> 10:24.373
I AM NOW KNOWN AS FOOFY NO-NO.

10:24.457 --> 10:26.334
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

10:26.417 --> 10:28.794
{\an1}ROCKO, I HAVE COME
TO MAKE AMENDS.

10:28.878 --> 10:30.463
PLEASE ACCEPT
THESE TURNIPS

10:30.546 --> 10:32.423
{\an1}AS A TOKEN
OF MY APOLOGIES

10:32.506 --> 10:34.884
{\an1}AND AS A SYMBOL
OF ETERNAL FRIENDSHIP.

10:34.967 --> 10:37.511
{\an1}ALSO, THIS LOVELY
THREE-SPEED BLENDERIZER.

10:37.595 --> 10:39.388
AND BACON-IN-A-BOX.

10:39.472 --> 10:41.140
BUT THAT'S NOT ALL.

10:41.223 --> 10:42.767
HERE'S FIVE BUCKS.

10:42.850 --> 10:44.727
UH, DINGO?

10:44.810 --> 10:45.936
AND LASTLY...

10:46.020 --> 10:47.605
A REQUEST.

10:47.688 --> 10:49.148
UH, YES?

10:49.231 --> 10:52.568
I WANT YOU TO PUNCH ME
IN THE NOSE.

10:52.651 --> 10:54.403
UH, UH, WHAT?!

10:54.487 --> 10:56.781
FOR ALL THE SUFFERING
I HAVE PUT YOU THROUGH

10:56.864 --> 10:58.532
FOR ALL THE PAIN
I HAVE CAUSED.

10:58.616 --> 11:00.409
UH, DINGO?

11:00.493 --> 11:03.412
PLEASE, ROCKO, FREE ME
FROM THAT WHICH I WAS

11:03.496 --> 11:06.123
{\an1}SO THAT I CAN BECOME ONE
WITH THE UNICORN.

11:06.207 --> 11:07.208
(<i> honking horn</i> )

11:09.877 --> 11:11.420
EH... DINGO?

11:11.504 --> 11:12.755
FOOFY NO-NO.

11:12.838 --> 11:14.799
UH, FOOFY NO-NO,
I'VE BEEN

11:14.882 --> 11:16.425
AFRAID OF YOU ALL MY LIFE

11:16.509 --> 11:18.761
{\an1}AND TODAY I WAS GOING
TO STAND UP TO YOU

11:18.844 --> 11:19.970
ONCE AND FOR ALL

11:20.054 --> 11:22.431
BUT IF I'VE LEARNED
ANYTHING FROM ALL THIS

11:22.515 --> 11:23.432
IT'S THAT VIOLENCE

11:23.516 --> 11:24.934
ISN'T GOING TO SOLVE ANYTHING.

11:25.017 --> 11:26.602
IT ONLY MAKES THINGS
WORSE.

11:26.685 --> 11:27.561
AND THAT'S WHY

11:27.645 --> 11:29.605
I CAN'T PUNCH YOU
IN THE NOSE.

11:29.688 --> 11:31.273
PLEASE, ROCKO.

11:31.357 --> 11:32.149
OKAY!

11:33.025 --> 11:34.902
{\an1}(<i> nasally</i> ):
FANK YOU SO MUSH.

11:38.364 --> 11:40.574
{\an1}I'M SORRY YOU HAD
TO SEE THAT, SPUNKY.

11:40.658 --> 11:42.451
{\an1}WHAT I DID JUST NOW
WAS WRONG.

11:42.535 --> 11:44.954
I SHOULD'VE STUCK BY MY DECISION

11:45.037 --> 11:45.955
TO AVOID VIOLENCE.

11:46.038 --> 11:47.581
THAT'S WHAT I SHOULD'VE DONE.

11:47.665 --> 11:49.625
{\an1}YOU LEAVE
OUR FRIEND ALONE

11:49.708 --> 11:50.793
YOU BIG BULLY.

11:50.876 --> 11:52.962
{\an8}LET'S ROAST HIS ONION!

11:53.045 --> 11:54.630
{\an5}LET'S GET HIM!

11:53.045 --> 11:54.630
{\an1}YEAH!

11:54.713 --> 11:55.464
{\an1}COME ON!

11:55.548 --> 11:57.466
Heff:
YOU PICK ON ROCKO...

11:57.550 --> 11:59.885
ON THE OTHER HAND,
HE DID SAY PLEASE.

11:59.969 --> 12:01.053
AND YET, STILL

12:01.137 --> 12:03.556
I KNOW INSIDE
THAT WHAT I DID WAS WRONG

12:03.639 --> 12:05.808
{\an1}BECAUSE THAT'S NOT
THE KIND OF PERSON I AM.

12:05.891 --> 12:06.976
NOT AT ALL.

12:07.059 --> 12:09.145
I MEAN,
WE ALL HAVE CERTAIN STANDARDS

12:09.228 --> 12:10.980
THAT WE SHOULD TRY TO PRACTICE

12:11.063 --> 12:12.481
AND FOLKS AROUND THE COUNTRY

12:12.565 --> 12:13.816
HAVE A CONTRACT
WITH THIS COUNTRY

12:13.899 --> 12:15.901
THAT DOESN'T ALLOW US
TO SAY CERTAIN WORDS.

12:29.415 --> 12:32.042
Rocko:
OH, WHAT A GORGEOUS DAY.

12:32.126 --> 12:34.044
{\an1}WE OUGHT TO GO OUT
AND ENJOY IT.

12:34.128 --> 12:35.171
UH-HUH.

12:35.254 --> 12:36.755
{\an5}RIGHT.

12:35.254 --> 12:36.755
(<i> doorbell rings</i> )

12:39.049 --> 12:41.594
HI, ROCKO.

12:41.677 --> 12:42.887
HIYA, HEFFER.

12:42.970 --> 12:44.180
UH-HUH.

12:44.263 --> 12:45.681
RIGHT.

12:45.764 --> 12:48.350
HOW ABOUT A FRIENDLY GAME
OF BASEBALL?

12:48.434 --> 12:49.935
BASEBALL? YOU BET!

12:50.019 --> 12:51.896
RIGHT, HEFF?

12:51.979 --> 12:53.522
RIGHT.

12:53.606 --> 12:54.774
WE'LL BE OUT IN A SEC.

12:54.857 --> 12:56.650
JUST GOT TO GET MY GLOVE.

12:57.610 --> 13:00.613
{\an1}HEY, BATTER, BATTER,
BATTER, BATTER, BATTER--

13:00.696 --> 13:01.739
SWING!

13:01.822 --> 13:03.616
WHOA... OOH!

13:03.699 --> 13:04.617
WHOOP.

13:04.700 --> 13:05.576
NOT GOOD.

13:05.659 --> 13:07.119
TURTLE ON HIS BACK

13:07.203 --> 13:09.079
IN THE SUN, BRIGHT SUN.

13:09.163 --> 13:10.915
OW. MY RETINAS ARE MELTING.

13:13.626 --> 13:15.419
(<i> grunting</i> )

13:15.503 --> 13:18.047
AH, THAT'S BETTER.

13:18.631 --> 13:20.466
(<i> thunder</i> )

13:20.549 --> 13:21.800
UH-OH.

13:21.884 --> 13:23.052
NOT GOOD.

13:23.135 --> 13:26.305
TURTLE ON HIS BACK IN THE RAIN.

13:26.388 --> 13:28.307
(<i> grunting</i> )

13:29.642 --> 13:30.976
OH, DEAR!

13:32.937 --> 13:35.731
(<i> sneezing</i> )

13:35.814 --> 13:38.400
(<i> honking</i> )

13:38.484 --> 13:39.735
{\an1}HERE YOU GO,
FILBURT.

13:39.818 --> 13:42.738
I'M FEELING ACHY
AND FEVERISH

13:42.821 --> 13:44.573
AND INFLAMMATIOUS.

13:44.657 --> 13:48.410
{\an1}DR. HEFF SAYS YOU NEED
A GOOD DOSE OF TV.

13:48.494 --> 13:51.914
MY MOTHER USED TO READ TO ME
WHEN I WAS SICK.

13:51.997 --> 13:54.750
READ?! ARE YOU NUTS?

13:54.833 --> 13:57.586
NOBODY READS ANYMORE.

13:57.670 --> 13:59.421
I'VE GOT JUST THE CURE.

14:00.506 --> 14:03.926
<i>THE REALLY REALLY BIG BOOK</i>
<i>OF FAIRY TALES.</i>

14:06.220 --> 14:08.764
"ONCE UPON A TIME..."

14:08.847 --> 14:10.182
YAWN.

14:10.266 --> 14:12.142
"...THERE WERE
THREE BEARS--"

14:12.226 --> 14:13.143
{\an3}WAIT.

14:13.227 --> 14:14.311
IS THIS THE ONE

14:14.395 --> 14:15.980
WITH THE PORRIDGE THING?

14:16.063 --> 14:17.648
WELL, YES.

14:17.731 --> 14:19.692
OH, I WAS AFRAID OF THAT.

14:19.775 --> 14:22.319
PORRIDGE MAKES ME NAUSEOUS.

14:22.403 --> 14:25.781
I'M NAUSEOUS,
I'M NAUSEOUS, I'M NAUSEOUS.

14:25.864 --> 14:27.449
RIGHT. SORRY.

14:27.533 --> 14:28.617
HERE'S ANOTHER ONE.

14:28.701 --> 14:30.119
(<i> clears throat</i> )

14:30.202 --> 14:31.495
"ONCE UPON A TIME

14:31.579 --> 14:34.123
"THERE WERE TWO CHILDREN
WHO LIVED IN THE WOODS.

14:34.206 --> 14:36.667
ONE WAS NAMED HANSEL
AND THE OTHER WAS--"

14:36.750 --> 14:37.793
DEBBIE!

14:37.876 --> 14:38.627
OOH!

14:38.711 --> 14:41.005
I'VE NEVER HEARD
THAT ONE BEFORE.

14:41.088 --> 14:42.715
ONE DAY, HANSEL AND <i> DEBBIE</i>

14:42.798 --> 14:44.717
WERE ON THEIR WAY HOME
FROM THE--

14:44.800 --> 14:45.884
Heffer:
CIRCUS!

14:45.968 --> 14:48.137
YES, THE CIRCUS.

14:48.220 --> 14:49.638
AND OFF THEY SKIPPED

14:49.722 --> 14:52.558
{\an1}<i>MERRILY INTO THE DARK</i>
<i>AND SCARY FOREST.</i>

14:52.641 --> 14:54.685
♪ ...TRA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA ♪

14:54.768 --> 14:57.479
♪ TRA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA ♪

14:57.563 --> 14:58.522
♪ TRA-LA-LA-- ♪

14:58.606 --> 15:02.192
{\an5}Heff:
"SHORTCUT TO HANSEL
AND DEBBIE'S HOUSE."

15:02.276 --> 15:03.652
HOW CONVENIENT.

15:03.736 --> 15:04.528
I AM SUSPICIOUS.

15:04.612 --> 15:08.324
COME ON, WHERE'S
YOUR SENSE OF ADVENTURE?

15:08.407 --> 15:09.533
{\an1}OKAY.

15:09.617 --> 15:12.661
♪ TRA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA ♪

15:12.745 --> 15:14.580
♪ TRA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA... ♪

15:14.663 --> 15:17.124
{\an5}Rocko:
<i>"SO OFF THEY WENT</i>
<i>INTO THE FOREST</i>

15:17.207 --> 15:19.835
<i>UNAWARE OF THE EVIL</i>
<i>THAT LURKED AHEAD."</i>

15:19.918 --> 15:21.837
(<i> cackling</i> )

15:21.920 --> 15:24.048
(<i> sneezing</i> )

15:24.131 --> 15:26.550
(<i> sniffling</i> )

15:26.634 --> 15:30.679
(<i> cackling again</i> )

15:30.763 --> 15:33.724
(<i> bird calling</i> )

15:33.807 --> 15:36.852
{\an1}I FEAR WE HAVE
MERRILY SKIPPED TOO FAR

15:36.935 --> 15:38.854
AND HAVE LOST OUR WAY.

15:38.937 --> 15:41.023
WHAT ABOUT THE TRAIL
OF BREATH MINTS

15:41.106 --> 15:42.900
YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO LEAVE?

15:42.983 --> 15:43.942
I DON'T KNOW.

15:44.026 --> 15:46.862
{\an1}BUT THE BIRDS AROUND HERE
SMELL MINTY FRESH.

15:46.945 --> 15:47.863
JOHN...

15:47.946 --> 15:49.615
MARCIA...

15:49.698 --> 15:53.160
(<i> background creaking</i> )

15:53.243 --> 15:54.578
OH, LOOK.

15:54.662 --> 15:57.623
A COTTAGE MADE ENTIRELY
OF HEALTHY SNACKS.

15:57.706 --> 15:59.249
HEALTHY SNACKS?!

15:59.333 --> 16:01.377
WHAT FUN IS THAT?

16:01.460 --> 16:03.212
THE HOUSE IS MADE OF PIZZA.

16:05.547 --> 16:08.634
{\an1}NO, IT'S NOT,
IT'S MADE OF HEALTHY SNACKS.

16:09.468 --> 16:12.888
{\an1}Heffer:
PIZZA!

16:12.971 --> 16:13.764
HEALTHY SNACKS!

16:13.847 --> 16:14.765
PIZZA!

16:14.848 --> 16:16.558
HEALTHY SNACKS!

16:16.642 --> 16:17.726
PIZZA!

16:17.810 --> 16:18.977
HEALTHY SNACKS!

16:19.061 --> 16:20.270
PIZZA!

16:20.354 --> 16:21.438
Filburt:
HEY!

16:21.522 --> 16:22.815
YOU'RE BOTH WRONG.

16:22.898 --> 16:25.442
THE HOUSE IS MADE
OF FISH STICKS.

16:29.655 --> 16:32.825
{\an1}IMAGINE THAT,
A FISH STICK HOUSE.

16:32.908 --> 16:35.327
WELCOME, YOU LOST CHILDREN.

16:35.411 --> 16:37.454
COME IN AND EAT MY HOUSE.

16:37.538 --> 16:40.082
I GOT PLENTY OF TARTAR SAUCE.

16:40.165 --> 16:43.711
NOW, REMEMBER, I'M THE WITCH.

16:47.506 --> 16:50.801
THAT'S IT, EAT UP.

16:50.884 --> 16:53.053
GET GOOD AND FAT.

16:53.137 --> 16:54.179
UH, HANSEL?

16:54.263 --> 16:56.432
I DON'T THINK
COMING TO THIS HOUSE

16:56.515 --> 16:57.933
WAS SUCH
A GOOD IDEA.

16:59.184 --> 17:00.936
MAGIC BEANS?

17:01.019 --> 17:02.312
GOOD IDEA.

17:05.357 --> 17:06.900
THESE AREN'T FOR EATING.

17:06.983 --> 17:08.777
THESE ARE MAGIC BEANS.

17:08.861 --> 17:10.738
HERE, WATCH.

17:13.991 --> 17:15.784
(<i> rumbling</i> )

17:15.867 --> 17:17.493
{\an3}HOLD ON!

17:18.412 --> 17:20.789
WAIT!

17:20.873 --> 17:24.417
I WAS GOING TO MAKE AN ESPRESSO.

17:26.627 --> 17:28.297
(<i> cages creaking</i> )

17:28.380 --> 17:29.506
(<i> thumping</i> )

17:29.590 --> 17:32.551
Filburt:
FEE, FI, FO, FUM.

17:32.634 --> 17:34.344
SOMETHING STINKS.

17:34.428 --> 17:37.014
(<i> both screaming</i> )

17:37.097 --> 17:40.350
{\an5}Rocko:
<i>"AND OFF WENT THE EVIL GIANT</i>
<i>GRANDMA TO HER CASTLE."</i>

17:41.477 --> 17:43.479
HEY, GRANDMA

17:43.562 --> 17:46.690
{\an1}THOSE ARE MIGHTY BIG
TEETH YOU HAVE.

17:46.774 --> 17:48.233
ALL THE BETTER TO CHEW UP

17:48.317 --> 17:50.402
MY NUTRITIONAL
DAILY REQUIREMENT

17:50.486 --> 17:51.820
OF CHILDREN LIKE YOU.

17:51.904 --> 17:54.490
{\an1}HOW COME EVERYBODY
WANTS TO EAT US?

17:54.573 --> 17:57.659
{\an1}HEY, DEBBIE, DON'T YOU HAVE
A HAIRPIN OR SOMETHING?

17:57.743 --> 17:59.495
NO, BUT I HAVE A KEY.

17:59.578 --> 18:02.706
TEETH, DON'T FAIL ME NOW.

18:03.916 --> 18:04.249
WHAT?

18:10.047 --> 18:12.883
(<i> growling</i> )

18:22.851 --> 18:26.522
(<i> cackling</i> )

18:26.605 --> 18:29.775
I'LL GRIND YOUR BONES
TO MAKE MY--

18:29.858 --> 18:31.026
PORRIDGE!

18:31.109 --> 18:32.528
PORRIDGE?

18:32.611 --> 18:34.071
OOH...

18:34.154 --> 18:36.031
I'M NAUSEOUS, I'M NAUSEOUS...

18:36.115 --> 18:37.241
GOOD ONE, HANSEL.

18:37.324 --> 18:38.575
WHERE YOU GOING?

18:38.659 --> 18:40.536
HANSEL, GIVE ME A HAND.

18:40.619 --> 18:42.037
PUT YOUR THUMB HERE.

18:42.120 --> 18:44.081
THERE. GOT IT.

18:44.164 --> 18:45.916
I'M NAUSEOUS, I'M NAUSEOUS...

18:45.999 --> 18:47.626
I'M BETTER NOW.

18:47.709 --> 18:50.462
Both:
YOU'LL NEVER CATCH US.

18:50.546 --> 18:52.548
WHY, YOU PESKY KIDS!

18:52.631 --> 18:53.882
WHOA...

18:53.966 --> 18:55.259
RUN!

18:55.342 --> 18:58.345
{\an3}OH...

18:58.428 --> 19:01.890
{\an5}Rocko:
<i>"THE HUNGRY GIANT</i>
<i>LOST HER LUNCH."</i>

19:01.974 --> 19:02.307
(<i> screaming</i> )

19:05.519 --> 19:09.690
(<i> still screaming</i> )

19:11.400 --> 19:13.610
(<i> still screaming</i> )

19:13.694 --> 19:17.406
{\an3}SHUT UP!

19:17.489 --> 19:21.785
<i>"LUCK AND ATMOSPHERIC CONDITIONS</i>
<i>WERE ON THEIR SIDE."</i>

19:21.869 --> 19:22.911
Both:
WHEW.

19:22.995 --> 19:24.580
THAT WAS A CLOSE ONE.

19:24.663 --> 19:26.748
Filburt:
YOU WANT THAT ESPRESSO NOW?

19:27.332 --> 19:31.295
(<i> screaming</i> )

19:31.378 --> 19:33.213
I COULD MAKE TEA.

19:37.676 --> 19:40.429
CREAM OR SUGAR?

19:40.512 --> 19:41.513
(<i> screaming</i> )

19:44.892 --> 19:48.437
(<i> elevator ringing</i> )

19:48.520 --> 19:50.105
IT'S ALL CLEAR.

19:50.188 --> 19:51.315
Both:
HUH?

19:51.398 --> 19:53.984
YOU CAN'T GO TO THE BALL
LIKE THAT.

19:54.067 --> 19:55.986
WHAT?

19:56.069 --> 19:58.405
OH, YEAH.

19:59.948 --> 20:03.076
{\an1}LOOK, HEFF,
I'M A PRINCE.

20:03.160 --> 20:04.912
ME NEXT, DO ME NEXT.

20:04.995 --> 20:07.998
HOLD YOUR HORSES, DUTCH BOY.

20:08.498 --> 20:11.001
WOW!

20:11.084 --> 20:13.420
I FEEL PRETTY.

20:13.503 --> 20:15.005
CALL ME...

20:15.088 --> 20:18.175
CINDERHEFFER.

20:18.258 --> 20:20.093
DON'T WE GET
A COACH WITH THIS?

20:20.177 --> 20:23.013
DON'T RUSH THE MAGIC.

20:23.096 --> 20:24.890
{\an1}AH, YES.

20:24.973 --> 20:26.433
THAT'LL DO.

20:30.479 --> 20:33.148
THANKS.

20:33.231 --> 20:33.440
NO PROBLEM.

20:35.233 --> 20:36.318
UH...

20:36.401 --> 20:37.653
GIDDY-UP?

20:37.736 --> 20:39.988
I WANT SOMEONE
TO DANCE WITH ME.

20:40.072 --> 20:41.448
Rocko:
<i>"BUT ONE WRONG TURN SENT THEM</i>

20:41.531 --> 20:44.493
<i>RIGHT BACK</i>
<i>TO WHERE THEY STARTED."</i>

20:44.576 --> 20:46.662
THESE WOODS
LOOK AWFULLY FAMILIAR.

20:46.745 --> 20:48.372
{\an5}Heffer:
MAYBE WE OUGHT
TO TURN BACK.

20:50.582 --> 20:53.001
STOP RIGHT THERE.

20:53.085 --> 20:54.878
(<i> all screaming</i> )

20:54.962 --> 20:56.171
THE WITCH!

20:56.254 --> 20:58.507
THAT'S ME, THE WITCH.

20:58.590 --> 21:00.175
STAY.

21:00.259 --> 21:02.094
YES, IT IS I

21:02.177 --> 21:04.012
AND I'VE COME
BEARING GIFTS.

21:04.096 --> 21:08.183
{\an1}WOULD YOU LIKE
A JUICY BLUE APPLE?

21:08.266 --> 21:09.184
{\an3}SURE.

21:09.267 --> 21:11.478
CINDERHEFFER, DON'T.

21:13.397 --> 21:15.190
WASH IT DOWN

21:15.273 --> 21:18.193
WITH A DELICIOUS BEVERAGE?

21:18.276 --> 21:19.194
{\an3}GREAT!

21:19.278 --> 21:20.195
CINDERHEFFER!

21:20.278 --> 21:22.280
(<i> gulping</i> )

21:22.364 --> 21:24.074
AH...

21:24.157 --> 21:25.200
(<i> belching</i> )

21:25.283 --> 21:26.994
OKAY.

21:27.077 --> 21:31.206
AND HOW ABOUT
AN AFTER-DINNER MINT?

21:31.289 --> 21:33.542
OOH.

21:33.625 --> 21:35.168
CINDERHEFFER, NO!

21:43.844 --> 21:48.432
CINDERHEFFER, SPEAK TO ME.

21:48.515 --> 21:51.351
{\an1}NOW HE'LL NEVER GET
TO DANCE AT THE BALL.

21:53.895 --> 21:58.400
{\an5}Rocko:
<i>"THE FOREST WAS</i>
<i>A SAD, SAD PLACE THAT DAY."</i>

22:08.910 --> 22:10.912
WAIT A MINUTE, YOU!

22:10.996 --> 22:12.622
ME?

22:12.706 --> 22:16.585
YOU DID THIS TO CINDERHEFFER
AND NOW YOU'LL PAY.

22:16.668 --> 22:19.004
NO, I WON'T.

22:25.343 --> 22:27.262
Rocko:
<i>"A GIANT?"</i>

22:27.346 --> 22:30.098
{\an5}Rocko:
OH, LOOK,
THE WITCH'S GLASS SHOES.

22:30.182 --> 22:33.310
THESE JUST MIGHT
FIT CINDERHEFFER.

22:37.731 --> 22:40.442
I'M ALIVE!

22:40.525 --> 22:43.487
AND I'M A REAL BOY.

22:46.823 --> 22:49.451
(<i> playing fanfare</i> )

22:49.534 --> 22:53.580
(<i> crowd cheering</i> )

22:57.751 --> 22:59.961
MUSH!

23:00.045 --> 23:01.046
{\an3}OATMEAL!

23:01.129 --> 23:02.881
PORRIDGE!

23:02.964 --> 23:04.466
Heffer:
WHEE!

23:04.549 --> 23:08.303
{\an5}Rocko:
"AND THEY LIVED
HAPPILY EVER AFTER.

23:08.386 --> 23:09.638
THE END."

23:09.721 --> 23:11.056
WHEW.

23:09.721 --> 23:11.056
WHEW.

23:11.139 --> 23:13.350
THAT STORY REALLY DID THE TRICK.

23:13.433 --> 23:15.519
I FEEL LIKE A MILLION BUCKS.

23:17.521 --> 23:20.482
I'LL RETURN THE FAVOR SOMEDAY.

23:20.565 --> 23:22.818
♪ TRA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA... ♪

23:22.901 --> 23:24.027
(<i> sneezing</i> )

23:24.111 --> 23:25.237
(<i> sneezing</i> )

23:25.320 --> 23:26.238
(<i> sniffling</i> )

23:26.321 --> 23:28.156
BLESS YOU.

23:28.240 --> 23:31.493
(<i> sniffling</i> )

23:31.576 --> 23:32.410
{\an1}(<i> stuffed up</i> ):
THANKS.

